---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Accessibility Checklist | Learn Web Design With Quinton Jason"
  description="A final accessibility checklist for ART 3020 projects covering headings, alt text, labels, keyboard navigation, focus states, contrast, and reduced motion."
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-heading">
        <p class="eyebrow">Accessibility Checklist</p>
        <h1>Review accessibility before every submission.</h1>
        <p class="lede">
          Accessibility is not one final tool scan. Use this checklist manually
          before submitting each project.
        </p>
      </div>

      <section class="project-brief-section project-checklist">
        <h2>Manual Checklist</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Headings are in order and describe the page structure.</li>
          <li>Images have useful alt text or are intentionally decorative.</li>
          <li>Form fields have visible labels connected to their inputs.</li>
          <li>Keyboard navigation works with Tab, Shift+Tab, Enter, Space, and Escape when needed.</li>
          <li>Focus states are visible on links, buttons, form fields, and custom controls.</li>
          <li>Color contrast is sufficient for body text, links, buttons, and important UI states.</li>
          <li>Animations respect reduced motion when motion is heavy or repeated.</li>
          <li>Links and buttons use clear text that makes sense out of context.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="callout">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">Tools Help, But They Do Not Finish The Job</p>
          <h2>Use Lighthouse and WAVE as support, not substitutes.</h2>
        </div>
        <p>
          Lighthouse and WAVE can catch useful issues, but they cannot tell
          whether your content makes sense, your alt text is useful, or your
          interaction is understandable. Always do a manual pass.
        </p>
        <div class="button-row">
          <a class="button button--primary" href="https://wave.webaim.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Open WAVE<span class="visually-hidden"> opens in a new tab</span></a>
          <a class="button" href="/lessons/web-accessibility/">Review Accessibility Lesson</a>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
